15/03/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Deputy Prime Minister Adriean Videanu announced on Monday (14 March) that he would run for mayor of Bucharest as the candidate of the ruling National Liberal Party-Democratic Party alliance. Videanu added that he would resign from his cabinet post by the end of this week. The ninth candidate to join the race, he is considered the frontrunner in the 3 April election. (Rompres, Ziarul financiar - 15/03/05) 
